PREFACE.

IN the text of this edition the MSS. have been followed rather than the emendations of editors, unless there seemed to be weighty reasons to the contrary. In placeS, how- ever, where A is certainly corrupt, the testimony of Donatus or other Scholiasts as to readings earlier than those in the Calliopian MSS. has been sometimes accepted, when sup- ported by intrinsic probability. In all but a few cases the limits of space have precluded a full statement of the argu- ments for and against doubtful readings, but in no instance has a decision been made! without careful consideration of all sides of the question.
